          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "30-ZN-67",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.954
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Two 67Zn samples were back-to-back as a set.",
                "The isotopic abundance of 67Zn sample material was",
                " 95.4% and each sample was vacuum evaporated on a",
                " tantalum backing 4.8 cm in diameter and 50 micron",
                " in thickness.",
                "The mass and the thickness of the forward sample were",
                " 9.864 mg and 680 ug/cm2.",
                "And those of the backward sample were 6.818 mg and",
                " 470 ug/cm2.",
                "The abundance of the 238U isotope in the monitor sample",
                "was better than 99.999%. The diameter and mass of the",
                "238U sample were 4.50 cm and 7.85 +- 0.10 microgram,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A twin gridded ionization chamber were used as",
                " alpha particle detector. The distances from the",
                " cathode to grid, grid to anode, and anode to shield",
                " were 61.0, 18.0 and 12.0 mm, respectively.",
                "The working gas was Kr+2.89%CO2 and the pressure was",
                " 1.30 atm.",
                "The high voltages for the cathode, grids and anodes",
                " were -1900, 0 and +1200 V, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A BF3 long counter was used as a neutron flux",
                " monitor for each run normalization."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "92-U-238(N,F),,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "92-U-238(N,F),,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "92-U-238(N,F)",
                        "target": "92-U-238",
